A 14-year-old boy was on Tuesday, remanded at Oregun Correctional Home, Lagos, by a magistrate court in Ikeja for molesting a five-year-old girl. The juvenile, a resident at Apapa, Lagos, pleaded guilty to the charge of defilement. The Prosecution Counsel. ASP Ezekiel Ayorinde on Tuesday told the court that the teenager committed the offence at his residence. He disclosed that the teenager sexually assaulted the girl, NAN reports. In ruling, Magistrate B.O. Osunsanmi ordered that the defendant be retained at the correctional home untill Feb. 12 for facts and sentencing.